fields.description:
When investigating wiki history changeset, there&#x27;s a "parent" link, which leads to

//bitbucket.org/<USER>/<REPO>/changeset/<NODEID>//

and clicking on it results in 404, because wiki changesets are located at

//bitbucket.org/<USER>/<REPO>/*wiki*/changeset/<NODEID>//

All disabled menu items are being displayed under the dashboard&#x27;s widgets when hovered.

With a little change at line 155 of the file &#x27;menu.css&#x27; the problem is solved.

Change from this:\\
{{{\\
#!css

#header ul#navigation-menu li.disabled:hover,\\
}}}

To this:\\
{{{\\
#!css

#header ul#navigation-menu li.disabled a:hover,\\
}}}

Tested on Firefox 3.6, Chrome 10 and Opera. While I on Linux at the moment, I couldn&#x27;t test the change on (argh) Microsoft Internet Explorer.

Hope this helps, and sorry for the poor English.

CI_Zip::read_dir second parameter seems to have no effect in WAMP environment.

Source of the problem is this part of the method:

{{{\\
#!php\\
if (FALSE !== ($data = file_get_contents($path.$file)))\\
{\\
$name = str_replace("\", "/", $path);\\
if ($preserve_filepath === FALSE)\\
{\\
$name = str_replace($root_path, &#x27;&#x27;, $name);\\
}

{code}
$this->add_data($name.$file, $data);
{code}

}\\
}}}

First command in the if-clause removes backslashes from path, but *$root_path* still contains the backslashes. I&#x27;ve solved the issue by adding a line to replace backslashes also from $root_path.

{{{\\
#!php\\
if (FALSE !== ($data = file_get_contents($path.$file)))\\
{\\
$name = str_replace("\", "/", $path);\\
$root_path = str_replace("\", "/", $root_path);\\
if ($preserve_filepath === FALSE)\\
{\\
$name = str_replace($root_path, &#x27;&#x27;, $name);\\
}

{code}
$this->add_data($name.$file, $data);
{code}

}\\
}}}

Not sure about side effects though.
